properties.name: body
properties.sample:
Hi {{tpoName}},

We warmly welcome the shortlisted candidates to Gemini Solutions!
As a part of your learning journey we are sharing a list of reading material that needs to be covered by you before you join us on {{doj}}.It would be exciting to work with you in the following days to come.

There are three books that must be read along with usage of MS office suite:

  1. [Operations - Theory of Constraints] The Goal by Eliyahu Goldratt
  2. [Finance] Options, Futures and Other Derivatives by John C Hull
  3. [Project Management] The Agile Coach -https://www.atlassian.com/agile
  4. [Efficient use of MS Office] - Website https://efficiency365.com/ and YouTube channel https://www.youtube.com/channel/UCpT8M17VVIZ0G1NZkQ9pxbw

You can also read through one of the most famous case studies of ERP implementation at BPCL India - https://www.icmrindia.org/free%20resources/casestudies/IT%20and%20Systems%20freecasestudyp1.htm

Also, sharing links from where you can download the books :

  1. The Goal by Eliyahu Goldratt -https://www.academia.edu/9716772/The_Goal_A_Process_of_Ongoing_Improvement_Third_Revised_Edition
  2. Options Futures and Other Derivatives by John C. Hull - https://epdf.pub/options-futures-and-other-derivatives-7th-edition.html

From Hull, you can read the following chapters: 1-8 (Basics), 14 (Markets in Developing countries), 16 (Futures Options), 20 (Value at risk) , 23 (Credit Derivatives), 34 (Mishaps).

Please share the caselets to us latest by {{link}}

Please connect with us in case of any other support required

Email :ashna.khurana@geminisolutions.com

Regards,
Team HR
